  "body": "I believe that we can use ES6 static get methods for propTypes, defaultProps, contextTypes, childContextTypes, and getChildContext rather than setting properties on the constructor.\n\nThis keeps everything neatly inside the class definition.\n\n``` javascript\n    class Foo extends React.Component {\n      static get propTypes() {\n        return {\n          bar: React.PropTypes.string.isRequired\n        };\n      }\n      render() {\n        return <span className=\"foo\" />;\n      }\n    }\n```\n\nI have updated the example in the blog and added a few tests.\n",
